    "Indeed, sinceξ = ln 1 + φ 1 -φ ∈ L ∞ (Q),there exist two real numbers r * and r *, depending on the structure of the system, such that-1 < r * ≤ φ(x, t) ≤ r * < 1 for every (x, t) ∈ Q.",
    "(3.9)Hence, the boundedness of ξ prevents the phase variable φ from approaching the singular values ±1, ensuring that φ remains within physically meaningful bounds throughout the evolution.4 The case when P is constantIn this section, we restrict ourselves to the case where the proliferation function P reduces to a positive constant and investigate the asymptotic behavior of the problem as α ↘ 0.",
